Honourable Sidi Bako, the former Lawmaker representing Obi in the fourth Assembly has emerged as the Chairman of New Nigeria People Party (NNPP) in Nasarawa State. Speaking shortly after he assumed the mantle of leadership, Sidi Bako said that the party is working towards unseating the ruling party in the forthcoming general election in the state. The newly elected chairman explained that the NNPP would strategise a way forward to bring a credible candidate that can be acceptable for the masses in the 2023 general election. He promised to sell the party ideology to the people of Nasarawa State for the party to be acceptable to the masses in the state. Also speaking, Honourable Umar Faruk, the north-central zonal Secretary who was optimistic with the way and manner people turn out en mass after quick notice about the delegates conference of the party in the state says that the party had already accepted the by people in the next general poll. Umar noted that the party’s plan was to bring credible leaders whose plans are to change the fortune of this country from the shackles of a mess they are into in the country. According to him,” The change matral has failed us what we need now is to bring people who can change the fortune of this country. “Within two weeks we are third strong political party in Nigeria if our leader senator Rabiu Kwankwaso declared his defection to join NNPP is going to be overwhelmed victory to NNPP,” Umar said. POLL Those who were elected to pilot the affairs of the party in the state include: Honourable Sidi Bako, Chairman, vice Chairman Partrick Ochini, Thomas N Luka, State Secretary, Alhaji Ladan Danlami Treasure, Danladi Nasiru Mairiga, Auditor general among others